title: iphone se2
description: As part of our efforts to reach our environmental goals,  iPhone SE (2nd generation) does not include a power adapter or EarPods. Included in the box is a USB‑C to Lightning cable that supports fast charging and is compatible with USB‑C power adapters and computer ports. We encourage you to re‑use your current USB‑A to Lightning cables, power adapters, and headphones which are compatible with this iPhone. But if you need any new Apple power adapters or headphones, they are available for purchase.

title: wi-1000x
description: Digital Noise Cancelling with Atmospheric Pressure Optimizing. Connect APP for Android /iOS to use Smart Listening technology to control your ambient sound settings. Ambient Sound mode to hear essential sound without taking your headphones off Battery life up to 10 hours (with wireless noise cancelling) / Hands free calling with vibration notification Wired cable solution let you connect in-flight entertainment

title: panda
description: Giant panda, (Ailuropoda melanoleuca), also called panda bear, bearlike mammal inhabiting bamboo forests in the mountains of central China. Its striking coat of black and white, combined with a bulky body and round face, gives it a captivating appearance that has endeared it to people worldwide. According to the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, fewer than 1,900 pandas are thought to remain in the wild.

title: CBF190TR
description: Honda has officially unveiled the all-new CBF190TR in the Chinese market. The modern-retro scrambler from the brand has been inspired by its older siblings like CB300R and CB650R. The bike has been specifically designed by Sundiro Honda, the brand’s Chinese arm to cater to the needs of millennials. With its unique styling and a promised accessible pricing, the Honda CBF190TR is expected to be a hit in China.
